ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot; Returned again unto Damascus.&quot; </div><div class="t m1709 x18 h2b y637 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What does he say it was the good pleasure of God to do? </div><div class="t m1863 x18 h2b y195b ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;To reveal His Son in me.&quot; </div><div class="t m1002 x18 h2b y1652 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Where was the Son revealed? </div><div class="t m1635 x18 h2b y1e5b ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What for? </div><div class="t m241a x26 h2b y1ad6 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;That I might preach Him among the heathen.&quot; </div><div class="t mfdc x18 h2b y13fd ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What then is necessary to the preaching of the Gospel? </div><div class="t m156d x18 h2b y1ffc ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">From what time does the apostle say he was separated to this </div><div class="t m192 x92 h2b y1656 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">work? </div><div class="t m1bca x26 h2b y1d03 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;From my mother&apos;s womb.&quot; </div><div class="t mf5f x26 h2b y17b7 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Of what was his call, after so much resistance, a manifestation? </div><div class="t m2a3c x26 h2b y135c ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;God . . . called me by His grace.&quot; </div><div class="t m2af x8b h34 y2269 ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTES. </div><div class="t m96f x18 h2b y1d56 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">I. Every man who receives the Gospel as truth, must receive </div><div class="t m2562 x92 h2b y17a3 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">it as the direct revelation of Jesus Christ, even though a human </div><div class="t m22ad x92 h2b y1146 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">instrument be used. The Gospel is not of man, but wholly super-</div><div class="t m2762 x92 h2b y1a98 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">natural. &quot;No man can say that Jesus is Lord, but by the Holy </div><div class="t m24eb xe h2b y1112 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ghost.&quot; I Cor. </div><div class="t mdd3 xf h34 y1112 ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">12 :</div><div class="t m8d6 xb h2b y1112 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m3e8 x26 h2b y1f6e ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m15b1 x74 h2b y18f0 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Read Acts 7 : 57-60; 8 : 1-3; 9 : I, 2; 22 : 4, 19, 20; 26:9-II, </div><div class="t m8f7 x92 h2b y1fa3 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">for a complete history of the persecution carried on by Paul </div><div class="t m1801 x92 h2b y1787 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">before his conversion, and of the spirit that animated him. He </div><div class="t mb29 x92 h2b y1194 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">certainly was not predisposed to Christianity. </div><div class="t m821 x26 h2b y2161 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m1b03 x74 h2b y1a05 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Note that &quot;the Jews&apos; religion &quot; was not the religion of God </div><div class="t m1548 xe h2b y1b3b ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and Christ. It consisted in the traditions of the fathers. It was </div><div class="t m1149 xe h2b y172f ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">all of man. Compare Matt. 15: 1-9; 23 :1-5. The contrast be-</div><div class="t m2633 xe h2b y17c4 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tween the false and the true is seen in that as soon as Paul saw </div><div class="t m1f4d xe h2b y1b1c ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the Lord he &quot;conferred not with flesh and blood.&quot; </div><div class="t m3cc x4d h21 y1f04 ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;Imme-</div><div class="t m241 xe h21 y1c82 ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">diately&quot;—he </div><div class="t me1e x50 h2b y1393 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">lost no time; he did not stand parleying. </div><div class="t m6f9 x26 h2b y1ac0 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m11f9 x74 h2b y1558 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The revelation of Christ in man is necessary in order that </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
